The paper deals with the design of small and effective convolutional neural networks for mobile/embedded applications, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves parameter binarization, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on ImageNet, which is a popular dataset in multimedia (cs.MM).
